Here’s a quick guide to help you get started:

---

🔑 Steps to Send a Pull Request
1. Fork the Repository
   - Go to firebase/firebase-android-sdk.
   - Click Fork (top-right corner) to create a copy under your GitHub account.

2. Clone Your Fork
   `bash
   git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/firebase-android-sdk.git
   cd firebase-android-sdk
   `

3. Create a Branch
   `bash
   git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
   `

4. Make Your Changes
   - Implement your fix or feature.
   - Follow Firebase’s coding style and contribution guidelines (see CONTRIBUTING.md in the repo).

5. Commit and Push
   `bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "Add feature/fix: description"
   git push origin feature/your-feature-name
   `

6. Open a Pull Request
   - Go back to your fork on GitHub.
   - Click Compare & pull request.
   - Fill in details about your changes and submit.

---

📌 Contribution Tips
- Check open issues first: Many improvements are already tracked in Issues (github.com in Bing).
- Run tests locally: Ensure your changes don’t break existing functionality.
- Follow CI requirements: Firebase uses automated checks; passing them is essential.
- Engage with maintainers: Be responsive to feedback on your PR.

