Recommended end-to-end architecture
- Ingest: Kafka for events; use connectors (Kafka Connect) to pull from APIs, DBs, IoT devices【1】.  
- Storage: Raw events → object store (S3/GCS/MinIO) or HDFS for large historical datasets【2】.  
- Processing: Use Spark for batch and ML workloads; use Flink for low-latency streaming where event-time correctness matters【2】.  
- Orchestration: Airflow to schedule batch jobs, trigger streaming jobs, and manage dependencies【3】.  
- Serving: Materialize results to OLAP store (e.g., Presto/Trino, BigQuery) or NoSQL for low-latency lookups.  

