Risks, trade-offs, and tips
- Complexity vs latency: True streaming (Flink) reduces latency but increases operational complexity; Spark is easier for mixed batch/stream workloads【2】.  
- Operational cost: Managed cloud services reduce ops burden but increase recurring cost; prototype locally to estimate resource needs【3】.  
- Data correctness: Use schema registry and idempotent producers to avoid duplicates; enforce retention and compaction policies in Kafka.  

